						<summary>

						<p>Broken stone lying in a field known as Turakapalle Pāṭimīndichēnu, about 6 km from the village.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 18th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that the land situated to the north of the boundary of Turakalapalle field is assigned to the god Allāḍanātha.</p>						

						</summary>
